This examples are intended to be used with GNU C (gcc).

This brief instruction explains how you can compile them.

1. Set LIXA environment variables:
   . /opt/lixa/bin/lixa_env.sh
2. Compile the interested C <programname> with this command line:
   gcc <programname>.c $(lixa-config -c -f -l -d) -o <programname>
   Example for example1.c
   gcc example1.c $(lixa-config -c -f -l -d) -o example1

NOTE: many examples require other open source or commercial resource managers
      that requires additional header files and libraries.
      Please look at LIXA reference guide for additional details.
